main event: An unidentified object was reported sighted near Moss Bluff, Florida on March 20, 1967, but the investigation concluded with insufficient data for evaluation.
interesting points: The object was observed moving three times as fast as a plane., Witnesses reported that the object glowed bright and appeared solid., The object reportedly rose and dropped suddenly while changing directions., Multiple witnesses, including an amateur astronomer, confirmed seeing the object., There was physical evidence of the sighting noted in the report.
